{"parse":{"title":"Pendilia","pageid":14159830,"revid":750074069,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Unreferenced\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"39\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/75px-Question_book-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/100px-Question_book-new.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"399\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>does not <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\">cite</a> any <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">sources</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pendilia&amp;action=edit\">improve this article</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing_with_Wiki_Markup/1\" title=\"Help:Introduction to referencing with Wiki Markup/1\">adding citations to reliable sources</a>. Unsourced material may be challenged and <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability#Burden_of_evidence\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">removed</a>.</span>  <small><i>(June 2015)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:122px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:A_Szent_Korona_el%C3%B6lr%C5%91l_2.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/A_Szent_Korona_el%C3%B6lr%C5%91l_2.jpg/120px-A_Szent_Korona_el%C3%B6lr%C5%91l_2.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"140\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/A_Szent_Korona_el%C3%B6lr%C5%91l_2.jpg/180px-A_Szent_Korona_el%C3%B6lr%C5%91l_2.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/A_Szent_Korona_el%C3%B6lr%C5%91l_2.jpg/240px-A_Szent_Korona_el%C3%B6lr%C5%91l_2.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1500\" data-file-height=\"1750\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:A_Szent_Korona_el%C3%B6lr%C5%91l_2.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/wiki/Holy_Crown_of_Hungary\" title=\"Holy Crown of Hungary\">Holy Crown of Hungary</a> having <i>pendilia</i>.</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:122px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Tesoro_de_Guarrazar_(M.A.N._Madrid)_01.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Tesoro_de_Guarrazar_%28M.A.N._Madrid%29_01.jpg/120px-Tesoro_de_Guarrazar_%28M.A.N._Madrid%29_01.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"388\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Tesoro_de_Guarrazar_%28M.A.N._Madrid%29_01.jpg/180px-Tesoro_de_Guarrazar_%28M.A.N._Madrid%29_01.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Tesoro_de_Guarrazar_%28M.A.N._Madrid%29_01.jpg/240px-Tesoro_de_Guarrazar_%28M.A.N._Madrid%29_01.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"581\" data-file-height=\"1880\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Tesoro_de_Guarrazar_(M.A.N._Madrid)_01.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Votive crown of the <a href=\"/wiki/Visigoth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Visigoth\">Visigoth</a> King <a href=\"/wiki/Recceswinth\" title=\"Recceswinth\">Recceswinth</a> (\u2020 672), part of the <a href=\"/wiki/Treasure_of_Guarrazar\" title=\"Treasure of Guarrazar\">Treasure of Guarrazar</a>. Made of gold and precious stones in the 2nd half of the 7th century. <a href=\"/wiki/National_Archaeological_Museum_of_Spain\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"National Archaeological Museum of Spain\">National Archaeological Museum of Spain</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Madrid\" title=\"Madrid\">Madrid</a>).</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Pendilia</b> (singular <b>pendilium</b>; from <a href=\"/wiki/Latin\" title=\"Latin\">Latin</a> <i>pendulus</i>, hanging) or <b>pendoulia</b> (the Greek equivalent), are <a href=\"/wiki/Pendant\" title=\"Pendant\">pendants</a> or dangling ornaments hanging from a piece of metalwork such as a <a href=\"/wiki/Crown_(headgear)\" title=\"Crown (headgear)\">crown</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Votive_crown\" title=\"Votive crown\">votive crown</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Crux_gemmata\" title=\"Crux gemmata\">crux gemmata</a>, or <a href=\"/wiki/Kamelaukion\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kamelaukion\">kamelaukion</a>, and are a feature of Early Medieval <a href=\"/wiki/Goldsmith\" title=\"Goldsmith\">goldsmith</a> work.  On crosses the pendilia may include the letters <a href=\"/wiki/Alpha_and_omega\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alpha and omega\">alpha and omega</a>, and on votive offerings, which were often designed to be hung over altars and where pendilia are at their largest and most spectacular, they may spell out whole words (see illustration).\n</p><p>The term is commonly used in <a href=\"/wiki/Coin_collecting\" title=\"Coin collecting\">coin collecting</a>. Pendilia are depicted on coins as jewels or pearls hanging from the sides of the crown, and occur frequently on coins of <a href=\"/wiki/Byzantine_emperors\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Byzantine emperors\">Byzantine emperors</a>. The pendilia which hung from the Emperors' crowns began with <a href=\"/wiki/Marcian\" title=\"Marcian\">Marcian</a>. Although the years saw the styles of crown change, the pendilia remained, at least through <a href=\"/wiki/Manuel_II_Palaiologos\" title=\"Manuel II Palaiologos\">Manuel II Palaiologos</a>. Surviving crowns with pendilia include the <a href=\"/wiki/Holy_Crown_of_Hungary\" title=\"Holy Crown of Hungary\">Holy Crown of Hungary</a> and many votive crowns of the <a href=\"/wiki/Treasure_of_Guarrazar\" title=\"Treasure of Guarrazar\">Treasure of Guarrazar</a> from <a href=\"/wiki/Visigothic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Visigothic\">Visigothic</a> Spain.\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1274\nCached time: 20180912042941\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.052 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.077 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 66/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 3955/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 9/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 6/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.022/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 818 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   53.933      1 Template:Unreferenced\n100.00%   53.933      1 -total\n 63.93%   34.477      1 Template:Ambox\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:14159830-0!canonical and timestamp 20180912042941 and revision id 750074069\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[{"lang":"de","url":"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pendilien","langname":"German","autonym":"Deutsch","*":"Pendilien"},{"lang":"es","url":"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pendulia","langname":"Spanish","autonym":"espa\u00f1ol","*":"Pendulia"}],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"Articles_lacking_sources_from_June_2015"},{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"All_articles_lacking_sources"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Numismatics"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Types_of_jewellery"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Medieval_art"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Crown_jewels"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Crux_gem